WEBVTT

21:36.929 --> 21:38.328
<i>Kim: Five minutes to air.</i>

21:38.397 --> 21:41.230
<i>First team in the studio,
please. Five minutes.</i>

21:41.300 --> 21:42.392
<i>Natalie:
Well, I've heard the rumor.</i>

21:42.468 --> 21:43.526
<i>Jeremy:
And I've heard the rumor.</i>

21:43.602 --> 21:44.501
-- <i>That's two...that's three.</i>
-- <i>Plus Kim.</i>

21:44.570 --> 21:45.833
Three people
have heard the rumor.

21:45.905 --> 21:47.430
So I think we're justified
in being nervous.

21:47.506 --> 21:49.099
I think we're justified
in being damn nervous,

21:49.175 --> 21:50.734
and I'm somebody
who can be, frankly, nervous

21:50.810 --> 21:52.175
-- without much justification at all.
-- I know.

21:52.244 --> 21:53.643
-- Elliott, have you heard the rumor?
-- Yes, I have.

21:53.712 --> 21:54.941
That's four.

21:55.014 --> 21:56.140
That's four people we know
who've heard the rumor.

21:56.215 --> 21:57.341
And that's only counting the people
we know who've heard the rumor.

21:57.416 --> 21:58.349
That's right.

21:58.417 --> 22:00.283
What exactly
does a ratings expert do?

22:00.352 --> 22:02.150
Well, presumably,
he raises ratings.

22:02.221 --> 22:04.815
-- What's wrong with our ratings?
-- Our ratings are fine.

22:04.890 --> 22:06.255
-- We come in third.
-- Consistently.

22:06.325 --> 22:08.054
-- Damn straight. -- We come
in third each and every week.

22:08.127 --> 22:09.561
The only way
we could possibly do better

22:09.628 --> 22:11.426
-- is if we came in first or second.
-- That's right.

22:11.497 --> 22:13.864
-- It's not like we're those clowns
in fourth. -- Bunch of losers.

22:13.933 --> 22:15.628
I honestly don't see
the logic in hiring someone

22:15.701 --> 22:17.897
to come in here and shake things
up in order to gain share points

22:17.970 --> 22:19.597
when our ratings
are perfectly fine.

22:19.672 --> 22:22.004
-- It's illogical. -- And yet
four people have heard the rumor.

22:22.074 --> 22:24.509
-- You guys hear about the ratings guy?
-- A full five people now.

22:24.577 --> 22:25.510
-- <i>Good show.</i>
-- Good show!

22:25.578 --> 22:26.545
I'm a little worked up
about this.

22:26.612 --> 22:27.545
-- As well you should be.
-- As well should we all.

22:27.613 --> 22:30.412
[Knock on door]
Come in.

22:30.483 --> 22:31.973
-- Hi.
-- Hello.

22:32.051 --> 22:33.314
-- What's up?
-- Dana, what are you wearing?

22:33.385 --> 22:35.911
-- Do you like it?
-- As a matter of fact, I do.

22:35.988 --> 22:38.252
Tell me something. Why would
the nickel back have set up

22:38.324 --> 22:41.817
5 yards off the line on
third and one inside the 50

22:41.894 --> 22:43.259
and they've been going
off tackle all day?

22:43.329 --> 22:45.764
<i>Well, you have to figure --
Excuse me, Dana.</i>

22:45.831 --> 22:48.766
Sweetie, Dana can tell when
you're staring at her breasts.

22:48.834 --> 22:50.802
-- I <i>wasn't.</i>
-- <i>It's okay.</i>

22:50.870 --> 22:54.864
-- I mean, my eyes naturally went there, but
now I'm fine. -- Why are you wearing that?

22:54.940 --> 22:56.237
I assume after the show
you're going directly

22:56.308 --> 22:57.366
to an important
business meeting.

22:57.443 --> 22:58.740
She's going
to a bachelorette party.

22:58.811 --> 23:00.210
Why are you wearing
those clothes?

23:00.279 --> 23:03.146
-- The bachelorette party is biker-themed.
-- It's biker-themed?

23:03.215 --> 23:04.808
It's biker-themed.

23:04.884 --> 23:07.683
We're all being picked up and
escorted to the party on Harleys.

23:07.753 --> 23:09.881
-- I'm going to ride on the
back of a hog. -- Yeah?

23:09.955 --> 23:12.287
-- I know the lingo. -- Listen,
have you heard the rumor?

23:12.358 --> 23:13.621
-- About the ratings guy?
-- Is it true?

23:13.692 --> 23:15.126
-- No. -- No, you haven't
heard the rumor?

23:15.194 --> 23:17.128
Yes, I've heard the rumor.
No, it isn't true.

23:17.196 --> 23:18.857
-- Really?
-- There's no ratings guy.

23:18.931 --> 23:20.421
Five people
have heard the rumor.

23:20.499 --> 23:21.591
Five people are wrong.

23:21.667 --> 23:24.329
-- Show me San Diego. Show me Oakland.
-- <i>Three</i> minutes <i>out.</i>

23:24.403 --> 23:26.303
Loading animation
one through five.

23:26.372 --> 23:28.272
-- <i>Loading sound 5.</i>
-- <i>Chyr0n's clear on 60?</i>

23:28.340 --> 23:29.774
-- It's clearing.
-- Oakland's up.

23:29.842 --> 23:31.776
Thank you, Dave.
Stop looking at my ass.

23:31.844 --> 23:34.108
No problem.

23:34.180 --> 23:36.547
My point is that it can't be
any old first date.

23:36.615 --> 23:40.483
The bar here is very high, not so much
because it'll be my first date with Dana,

23:40.553 --> 23:42.851
but because it'll be
Dana's first date with me,

23:42.922 --> 23:45.186
and I'm known in some parts
for my first date.

23:45.257 --> 23:46.884
In certain parts,
I have a rep.

23:46.959 --> 23:49.087
There's such a thing
as street cred. Dan...

23:49.161 --> 23:50.287
Listen to this.

23:50.362 --> 23:51.557
Tell them
about my street cred.

23:51.630 --> 23:54.292
-- [Laughs] Seriously...
-- Tell them about my rep.

23:54.366 --> 23:55.492
You don't have a rep.
You don't have street cred.

23:55.568 --> 23:56.626
Your last date
was 14 years ago,

23:56.702 --> 23:59.262
and you ended up with
a marriage and a divorce.

23:59.338 --> 24:00.965
Oh, in some parts --

24:01.040 --> 24:02.667
No, there are no parts.
Now, listen to this.

24:02.741 --> 24:05.802
<i>Dave: Two minutes to VTR.</i>
-- I <i>just</i> hung <i>up the</i> phone.

24:05.878 --> 24:07.141
What's the best news
I could have?

24:07.213 --> 24:09.147
You won a 4-week vacation
to someplace else?

24:09.215 --> 24:11.240
The best news I could have
for me.

24:11.317 --> 24:14.184
You got invited to Hillary
Clinton's fund-raising breakfast.

24:14.253 --> 24:17.587
I got invited to Hillary Clinton's
fund-raising breakfast --

24:17.656 --> 24:19.055
me, the first lady,

24:19.124 --> 24:21.024
scrambled eggs,
lively conversation.

24:21.093 --> 24:24.358
It turns out it wasn't that hard.
You know what you have to do?

24:24.430 --> 24:27.195
-- Write a check for $1,000?
-- That's right.

24:27.266 --> 24:31.032
But not everyone was given
that opportunity. I was asked.

24:31.103 --> 24:34.038
<i>They asked you for $1,000,
and you gave it to them.</i>

24:34.106 --> 24:35.631
That's incredible, Danny.

24:35.708 --> 24:37.767
I was picked, Casey.
I was identified.

24:37.843 --> 24:39.641
Yes, it's called
"being a mark."

24:39.712 --> 24:41.510
I gladly gave my money
to a good fight.

24:41.580 --> 24:43.605
Danny, Isaac's got enough to deal
with from the network right now

24:43.682 --> 24:45.411
without you getting
into a good fight.

24:45.484 --> 24:48.215
-- This isn't about politics. --
She's running for the Senate.

24:48.287 --> 24:49.652
