-- How was it?

27:16.802 --> 27:17.735
Fantastic.

27:17.803 --> 27:18.770
Good scrambled eggs?

27:18.837 --> 27:20.669
-- Excellent scrambled eggs.
-- Connection?

27:20.739 --> 27:22.537
Connection made,
my young friend.

27:22.608 --> 27:24.975
-- Does anybody care if I'm not part of
this? -- It's just as well, Natalie.

27:25.043 --> 27:26.477
There are gonna be some parts
of this story

27:26.545 --> 27:27.842
that are unsuitable
for mixed company.

27:27.913 --> 27:30.041
-- I have to edit tape.
-- Where did you say Dana was?

27:30.115 --> 27:32.447
She was up all night. And she called
and said she'd be in an hour late.

27:32.518 --> 27:34.008
She was skanking around town
all leathered up?

27:34.086 --> 27:35.019
-- <i>I guess</i> so.
-- Excellent.

27:35.087 --> 27:36.054
Hey, you're talking

27:36.088 --> 27:37.021
about the woman

27:37.089 --> 27:38.147
whose first date with me

27:38.223 --> 27:39.156
I'm planning.

27:39.224 --> 27:40.919
That was some pretty
interesting grammar.

27:40.993 --> 27:42.825
See you at the rundown.

27:42.895 --> 27:45.364
Casey, it was the best
breakfast of my life.

27:45.431 --> 27:47.525
For a thousand bucks,
I imagine it'd be up there.

27:47.599 --> 27:50.330
I was introduced to her.
She held out her hand.

27:50.402 --> 27:52.268
Hillary Clinton.

27:52.337 --> 27:53.771
There she was --

27:53.839 --> 27:56.103
the hair, the shoes,
and the whole thing.

27:56.175 --> 27:57.870
She said, "Dan, let me" --

27:57.943 --> 28:00.207
First of all,
she called me "Dan."

28:00.279 --> 28:02.145
