-- Okay.

31:58.717 --> 32:00.515
But first, you got
to date other women.

32:00.585 --> 32:02.110
Let's go back
to the beginning.

32:07.459 --> 32:10.554
<i>You are about five different
kinds of crazy, you know that?</i>

32:10.629 --> 32:12.563
I don't think this is
the time or place, do you?

32:12.631 --> 32:15.464
No, you're right. Let's discuss
this six months from now

32:15.534 --> 32:17.662
after I've had more
experience with psychos.

32:17.736 --> 32:19.261
I have to talk to Isaac now.

32:19.337 --> 32:21.863
-- What if I just flat-out refuse?
-- What do you mean?

32:21.940 --> 32:23.999
What if I just refuse
to go along with your plan?

32:24.076 --> 32:26.704
Then you do not get
the wonder that is me.

32:28.680 --> 32:30.239
I'm not sure I want
the wonder that is you.

32:30.315 --> 32:32.909
Well, that's entirely
up to you.

32:32.984 --> 32:34.281
-- Yes, it is. Okay.
-- That's right.

32:34.352 --> 32:37.083
-- Fine. -- I-l want
to kill you right now.

32:37.155 --> 32:38.680
Problem is that's not
the only thing

32:38.757 --> 32:40.418
you want to do with me
right now, is it?

32:40.492 --> 32:42.324
No, that's pretty much it.

32:42.394 --> 32:44.624
I have to talk to Isaac now.

32:44.696 --> 32:46.095
What's the problem here?

32:46.164 --> 32:49.031
He's mad 'cause I had
an epiphany and he didn't.

32:50.769 --> 32:54.069
This isn't happening.

32:56.374 --> 32:57.808
[Knock on door]

32:57.876 --> 32:59.742
-- Come in.
-- Hey.

32:59.811 --> 33:01.279
How was the hooker party?

33:01.346 --> 33:04.179
Biker party. It was fine.
How was therapy?

33:04.249 --> 33:07.685
-- I walked 1/10 of a mile
on the treadmill. -- Good.

33:10.756 --> 33:12.815
-- Who's the ratings guy?
-- <i>Now,</i> Dana, <i>don't</i> go --

33:12.891 --> 33:16.054
-- Who's the ratings guy?
-- His <i>name's</i> Sam Donovan.

33:16.128 --> 33:17.289
Is he good?

33:17.362 --> 33:20.195
-- No, I decided to hire a moron.
-- Isaac...

33:20.265 --> 33:21.426
I think he's the best
in the business.

33:21.500 --> 33:22.524
I think there's
no one else close.

33:22.601 --> 33:24.899
<i>Who do I answer to --
you or him?</i>

33:24.970 --> 33:26.199
<i>Well, that's not how</i> --

33:26.271 --> 33:28.296
Isaac, who do I answer to,
you or him?

33:28.373 --> 33:29.898
I want you to work
with him, Dana.

33:29.975 --> 33:33.240
I want you to make this work.
It'll just be a short while.

33:33.311 --> 33:35.678
-- You didn't have to do this.
-- We're in third place.

33:35.747 --> 33:38.216
-- We were ticking up on our own.
-- Not fast enough.

33:38.283 --> 33:40.183
Fast enough for you,
fast enough for us.

33:40.252 --> 33:41.686
Not fast enough for them.

33:43.255 --> 33:44.484
I got to tell you,

33:44.556 --> 33:47.491
the sight of you -- the sight of
Isaac Jaffee fearing for his job...

33:47.559 --> 33:49.152
I want you
to work with him, Dana.

33:49.227 --> 33:50.717
I want you to make this work.

33:55.000 --> 33:56.968
-- Is there a number?
-- <i>What?</i>

33:57.035 --> 33:59.231
ls there a set number
of women?

33:59.304 --> 34:00.237
I don't know.

34:00.305 --> 34:01.795
'Cause if there's
a set number of women,

34:01.873 --> 34:03.807
maybe you can just get them
out of the way, bing-bam-boom.

34:03.875 --> 34:07.470
-- <i>Bing-bam-boom?</i> -- <i>That was</i> me <i>getting
women out of the way really fast.</i>

34:07.546 --> 34:10.880
-- You don't think her epiphany
sounds insane? -- I sort of do, yeah.

34:10.949 --> 34:13.418
But she didn't run it by me, so this
is the kind of thing that happens.

34:13.485 --> 34:17.149
No, this is the kind of thing that
happens when she does run it by you,

34:17.222 --> 34:18.917
so I'm surprised to hear
you weren't involved.

34:18.989 --> 34:21.482
Turning on me isn't
going to solve anything.

34:24.663 --> 34:25.926
What did he say?

34:25.996 --> 34:29.159
His name's Sam Donovan.
He's supposed to be very good.

34:29.234 --> 34:32.329
-- VVell, did Isaac say why all of a sudden
he decided to -- -- What do you think?

34:32.404 --> 34:34.702
Natalie, let me have senior
staff at 10 minutes to air.

34:34.806 --> 34:36.831
-- Sure. By the way,
this plan -- -- Yeah.

34:36.875 --> 34:37.808
Never ran it by me.

34:37.876 --> 34:39.900
I'm going with my instincts
on this one.

34:39.978 --> 34:41.139
It shows.

34:42.714 --> 34:44.045
I got to get to work.

34:44.114 --> 34:46.344
-- Dana, I have dated women before.
-- You have not.

34:46.418 --> 34:49.820
What about that double date at Anthony
Anthony's with you and Gordon?

34:49.888 --> 34:52.152
It almost turned
very serious with that girl.

34:52.224 --> 34:54.248
-- What was her name? -- Ah, for
the life of me, I can't remember.

34:54.326 --> 34:57.023
That's 'cause you ended up sitting at the
bar with me watching “Sports Night.“

34:57.094 --> 34:59.564
-- What about Sally?
-- That wasn't dating.

34:59.631 --> 35:02.066
VVell, we slept together almost
every night for three months.

35:02.133 --> 35:03.658
-- Thanks for reminding me.
-- Dana...

35:03.735 --> 35:05.931
That wasn't dating. That was
two lonely and pathetic people

35:06.004 --> 35:08.701
slinking off after her
crappy, little 2:00 A.M. show,

35:08.773 --> 35:11.333
getting drunk,
and using each other for sex.

35:12.944 --> 35:15.413
-- That's not dating?
-- No.

35:15.480 --> 35:18.245
Okay, but still, can I just do that for
a little while and we'll call it --

35:18.316 --> 35:19.784
-- No, sir!
-- Listen...

35:19.851 --> 35:21.717
Casey, I have dated,
and I'm done.

35:21.786 --> 35:24.312
The next thing I have --
I want it to be serious.

35:24.389 --> 35:26.585
The last thing you had,
you were engaged.

35:26.658 --> 35:28.057
You got to trust me on this.

35:28.126 --> 35:29.560
No, I don't think I do
have to trust you on this.

35:29.628 --> 35:31.062
We have a magical
first kiss in my office --

35:31.129 --> 35:33.097
I do not deny it was magical.

35:33.164 --> 35:34.723
You better not deny
it was magical,

35:34.799 --> 35:36.893
because I took you
off your feet, woman.

35:36.968 --> 35:38.299
I rocked you back.

35:38.370 --> 35:40.099
I do not deny it.

35:40.171 --> 35:43.141
I plan our first date --
Moomba, Cafe des Artistes --

35:43.208 --> 35:45.142
Carriage rides are out,
by the way.

35:45.210 --> 35:47.178
They are not out.
They are back in.

35:47.245 --> 35:48.804
Yeah?
If you're from Akron.

35:48.880 --> 35:50.075
[sighs] Hey.

35:50.148 --> 35:53.243
I'm not saying I wouldn't
have had a good time.

35:53.318 --> 35:56.344
-- So, this woman comes along at
your biker party -- -- Deanna.

35:56.421 --> 35:58.321
This drunken,
bitter, lesbian woman.

35:58.390 --> 36:01.189
Now, why would you do that? Why would
you go to lesbian right there?

36:01.259 --> 36:04.320
-- Tell me you're not a homophobe. --
Are you saying in order to prove to you

36:04.396 --> 36:06.091
that I'm grown-up enough
to go outwith you,

36:06.164 --> 36:08.690
you're gonna make me go out and
find other women to sample first?

36:08.767 --> 36:11.031
-- I'm not even gonna ask for approval.
-- Thanks.

36:11.102 --> 36:12.399
-- Casey...
-- Dana...

36:12.470 --> 36:14.598
We'll have more time
to talk about this later.

36:14.673 --> 36:17.540
Just know that I want to give
us the best possible chance.

36:17.609 --> 36:19.475
So you're going to have me
date your friends?

36:19.544 --> 36:22.514
I gotta go.
You all right?

36:22.580 --> 36:24.548
Actually, I am frightened
of my own life,

36:24.616 --> 36:26.880
but I'll talk to you later.

36:26.952 --> 36:28.283
Good.

36:41.032 --> 36:43.126
[sniffs]

36:43.201 --> 36:45.363
[Chuckles]

36:48.606 --> 36:52.440
-- [ Sighs] I'm going to have
to live with this. -- Yes.

36:52.510 --> 36:54.535
She never returned my calls.

36:54.612 --> 36:56.273
That's pretty surprising.

36:56.348 --> 36:57.440
She never returned my calls,

36:57.515 --> 36:58.505
and I'm going to
have to live with this

36:58.583 --> 37:00.608
the rest of my natural life.

37:01.853 --> 37:03.947
It's out there now,

37:04.022 --> 37:07.458
and it's probably getting
blown all out of proportion.

37:09.594 --> 37:10.857
Listen.

37:10.929 --> 37:14.456
You can hear the whispers
from the treetops.

37:14.532 --> 37:16.967
You know a lie can make it
halfway around the world

37:17.035 --> 37:19.436
before the truth has a chance
to get its boots on?

37:19.504 --> 37:20.972
What are you,
Burl Ives all of a sudden?

37:21.039 --> 37:22.564
As a matter of fact,
that was Mark Twain.

37:22.640 --> 37:25.109
-- I know who it was.
-- And so do I.

37:25.176 --> 37:27.406
And I'm able to quote him
because I'm educated.

37:27.479 --> 37:29.345
<i>I know things.</i>

37:29.414 --> 37:32.076
-- You work your whole life,
and in an instant... -- Yes.

37:32.150 --> 37:34.517
I'm sure she's told
her friends by now.

37:34.619 --> 37:35.950
Let's go.

37:36.921 --> 37:38.719
-- It's just out there...
-- Danny...

37:38.790 --> 37:40.280
and it can't be gotten back.

37:40.358 --> 37:42.793
What do you think
I should do about this?

37:45.063 --> 37:46.758
I think you should do
what she tells you to do.

37:46.831 --> 37:48.094
She had a weird night
at a party.

37:48.166 --> 37:50.032
Things will look different
in the cold light of day.

37:50.101 --> 37:53.230
-- Do you think? -- Does the plan
include you're supposed to have sex?

37:53.304 --> 37:55.170
I don't know.
I assume it's an option.

37:55.240 --> 37:58.175
-- You've explained to her that the
plan is insane? -- I'm trying.

37:58.243 --> 38:00.143
-- You want me to take a whack at it?
-- No.

38:00.211 --> 38:04.148
-- What's going on? -- I wanted us to say
hello to Sam Donovan before the show started.

38:04.215 --> 38:05.580
I'm sorry?

38:05.650 --> 38:07.982
I said I wanted us
to say hello to Sam Donovan,

38:08.053 --> 38:10.420
the ratings consultant,
before the show started.

38:10.488 --> 38:11.751
I thought you said,

38:11.823 --> 38:14.417
“I was thinking about my dating
plan and realized I was mental.“

38:14.492 --> 38:15.653
No.

38:15.727 --> 38:18.219
-- <i>Where</i> is <i>he?</i>
-- <i>I don't know.</i>

38:18.296 --> 38:19.923
Can I just say that I've had
experience with this before

38:19.998 --> 38:21.693
and I think you're all a little
too worried about nothing?

38:21.766 --> 38:23.165
These guys tend
to be obnoxious,

38:23.234 --> 38:26.135
but I've found they're mostly
obsequious and starved for acceptance.

38:30.075 --> 38:32.169
"Boned" and "deboned"
mean the same thing.

38:32.243 --> 38:33.540
Would you give it a rest?

38:35.213 --> 38:37.614
Actually, Danny's right. These
guys just want to be liked.

38:37.682 --> 38:38.979
<i>We show him that he's
perfectly welcome here</i>

38:39.050 --> 38:40.609
<i>but make it clear
we do a good show,</i>

38:40.685 --> 38:43.416
it's our show, and we're reluctant
to have the network involved

38:43.488 --> 38:45.047
in creative
or editorial decisions.

38:45.123 --> 38:46.784
We can't do that.

38:46.858 --> 38:49.987
-- Why? -- 'Cause Isaac
wants me to work with him.

38:50.061 --> 38:51.859
-- Dana... -- I'm gonna
work with him, Casey.

38:51.930 --> 38:54.194
It's just for a few weeks.

38:54.265 --> 38:56.632
[Sighs]

39:01.539 --> 39:03.803
There's such a word
as "disheveled,"

39:03.875 --> 39:07.709
but “sheveled“ is nowhere to
be found in the dictionary.

39:07.779 --> 39:08.712
Danny...

39:08.780 --> 39:11.545
I'm just saying
English sucks.

39:16.054 --> 39:18.182
We're starting
to press the clock.

39:18.256 --> 39:20.122
Dave, do me a favor.
Get us at ready-1.

39:20.191 --> 39:23.024
<i>Kim, Elliott, go ahead
and do your pref light.</i>

39:28.133 --> 39:32.331
-- Exactly how many dates do
I have to go on -- -- Later.

39:35.840 --> 39:37.274
This is nice.

39:37.342 --> 39:39.834
This is like quiet time.

39:42.080 --> 39:43.411
The hell with it.

39:43.481 --> 39:45.813
Let's go and do the show,
and then --

39:45.884 --> 39:47.750
Excuse me.

39:47.819 --> 39:49.184
Are you Sam Donovan?

39:49.254 --> 39:50.653
Yeah. I was just looking
for my office.

39:50.722 --> 39:52.247
I'm Dana Whitaker.

39:52.323 --> 39:53.791
How you doin'?

39:53.858 --> 39:55.189
-- Dan Rydell.
-- Casey McCall.

39:55.260 --> 39:56.625
Good to meet you.

39:56.694 --> 39:58.219
If someone could just
point me toward my office...

39:58.296 --> 40:00.765
We got together like this
to welcome you.

40:00.832 --> 40:02.994
Thanks. My office?

40:03.067 --> 40:05.195
I'm sorry.
You don't have one yet.

40:05.270 --> 40:07.204
I'm sure Janie, our
office manager -- [Thud]

40:07.272 --> 40:10.970
-- That'll be taken care of
by the morning? -- Yeah.

40:11.042 --> 40:13.010
Who's the segment producer
tonight?

40:13.077 --> 40:14.772
-- I <i>am.</i>
-- <i>What's your top story</i> --

40:14.846 --> 40:16.610
-- Oakland or Ted Marchibroda?
-- Ted Marchibroda.

40:16.681 --> 40:18.149
Make it Oakland, will you?

40:18.216 --> 40:20.150
Move Marohibroda to the 10-block.
Fill with the wild card.

40:20.218 --> 40:22.243
-- Are you scripted in the ones?
-- Yeah, but --

40:22.320 --> 40:24.311
<i>Excuse me, Jeremy.
Sam, what are you doing?</i>

40:24.389 --> 40:27.484
-- Hmm? -- I said,
“What are you doing?“

40:27.559 --> 40:31.325
It's gonna be helpful if you get
used to not asking that question.

40:31.396 --> 40:32.591
Hang on.

40:32.697 --> 40:36.258
You can't just come in here
and start dictating policy.

40:36.301 --> 40:38.565
<i>Now, we're ready to work with
you as long as you understand</i>

40:38.636 --> 40:40.661
that this is our show
and we feel we do it well.

40:40.738 --> 40:43.537
You should also bear in mind that
Dana doesn't stand alone here.

40:43.608 --> 40:45.372
Unless you want your first
action as a consultant

40:45.443 --> 40:47.343
to cause a full-staff walkout,

40:47.412 --> 40:50.143
including the on-air talent and
producers, I'd downshift a little.

40:52.984 --> 40:57.319
You shouldn't think that just because I'm
looking at you while you're talking to me

40:57.388 --> 41:00.414
that I'm necessarily listening to
or caring about what you're saying.

41:00.491 --> 41:02.482
It's just something I do
to be polite.

41:02.560 --> 41:04.858
I was lying
on a beach in Bali.

41:04.929 --> 41:07.694
I got a phone call.
I got on a plane for 14 hours.

41:07.765 --> 41:10.826
I was hired to raise this show's
audience share 3 points.

41:10.902 --> 41:13.803
Just between you and me,
I'm gonna raise it 3 1/2.

41:13.871 --> 41:16.806
I'm not lacking in confidence
as far as that's concerned,

41:16.874 --> 41:18.933
and because of that,
I can say this --

41:19.010 --> 41:21.980
I honestly don't give a damn
if any of you work here or not.

41:31.956 --> 41:33.822
Who's the coordinating
producer tonight?

41:33.891 --> 41:35.381
I am.

41:35.460 --> 41:37.428
Well, I've got 10:55.

41:37.495 --> 41:40.226
You want to call places?

41:43.234 --> 41:44.724
Places, first team.

41:44.802 --> 41:46.236
Dana...

41:46.304 --> 41:47.237
Go ahead, guys.

41:47.305 --> 41:48.238
No, wait a second.

41:48.306 --> 41:49.705
It's okay. Go ahead.

41:49.774 --> 41:52.766
-- <i>You sure?</i>
-- <i>Yeah. Good show.</i>

42:00.218 --> 42:01.686
I'm not gonna like you
very much, am I?

42:01.753 --> 42:05.189
Oh, don't be ridiculous, Dana.
Everybody likes me.

42:05.256 --> 42:07.691
<i>Dave." In 3...2...</i>

42:07.759 --> 42:09.625
<i>Good evening.
From New York City,</i>

42:09.694 --> 42:11.753
<i>I'm Dan Rydell
alongside Casey McCall.</i>

42:11.829 --> 42:15.094
Those stories, plus “inside the
Playbook“ with Kelly Kirkpatrick,

42:15.166 --> 42:16.930
“Center Ice“
with Jack Jankowitz,

42:17.001 --> 42:19.595
and "The Infield Fly"
with Connie Morton in Chicago.

42:19.671 --> 42:21.833
All that coming up after this.

42:21.906 --> 42:25.342
You're watching “Sports Night“
on CSC, so stick around.

42:25.410 --> 42:27.071
<i>Dave." We're out.</i>

42:39.390 --> 42:40.721
<i>On the next "Sports Night"...</i>

42:40.792 --> 42:42.658
I'm frightened
every time I'm near him.

42:42.727 --> 42:43.853
You gotta face that fear.

42:43.928 --> 42:44.918
<i>If I allow you three</i>

42:44.996 --> 42:46.930
to go in there
and mess with my show,

42:46.998 --> 42:50.263
will it keep my staff
from losing their jobs?

42:50.335 --> 42:51.496
I can't make promises.

42:51.569 --> 42:53.628
Fire me or shut the hell up.

42:53.705 --> 42:55.935
It doesn't seem like he's
recovering as fast as we hoped.

42:56.007 --> 42:57.668
You've become a malcontent,
Danny.

42:57.742 --> 42:59.471
You've become
a secretary, Dana.

42:59.544 --> 43:01.808
-- No <i>one's blaming you.</i>
-- <i>Every0ne's blaming me!</i>

43:01.879 --> 43:03.278
-- We're in trouble.
-- I know.
